# Environment & Toolchain

SDKman is installed at `/usr/local/sdkman` (NOT `~/.sdkman`). Java, Quarkus CLI, and Gradle all require it.

Any shell command using `java`, `quarkus`, or `./gradlew` must source SDKman first:

```bash
source /usr/local/sdkman/bin/sdkman-init.sh && ./gradlew <task>
```

- Java: 25 (Amazon Corretto)
- Quarkus CLI: 3.34.6
- Gradle: 9.3.1 via wrapper — always use `./gradlew`, never a system Gradle

## Database

The PostgreSQL database runs on the **host only** — it is NOT reachable from inside the dev container.

- Port: `5436`, user: `postgres`, password: `xxx`, database: `document-ingestion-db`
- Start it on the host with: `bash start-db.sh`
- Never attempt to start the DB or run Flyway migrations from inside the container
- If a DB connection error occurs, report it to the user and ask them to run it on the host
